The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Torture deal soon 

 Washington, Dec. 15 (Reuters): Under bipartisan pressure, the White House appeared on the verge of a deal today with Senator John McCain on a law requiring the humane treatment of prisoners in US custody. 

 Theyre close but I cant say its done, said an official. The administration has been hit by scandal over the physical abuse of detainees by US soldiers in Iraq, Guantanamo Bay, Cuba, and Afghanistan. 

 Tobacco case 

 Chicago (Reuters): An Illinois court on Thursday reversed a $10.1 billion verdict against Philip Morris USA, ordering a lower court to dismiss the case in which the company was accused of defrauding customers into thinking light cigarettes were safer than regular ones. 

 China fire 

 Beijing (Reuters): A fire at the largest hospital in the northeastern Chinese city of Liaoyuan killed 33 people on Thursday, Xinhua reported. Rescuers found 19 bodies at the scene and 14 other people died in hospitals. 




